<!-- Railway watch paths (config-as-code):
     `railway.json` at the repo root pins `build.watchPatterns` so only real app
     changes trigger a redeploy. The workflow commits docs/spec changes constantly
     (every /refine, /draft, and the changelog on /release), so without this each of
     those commits to the deploy branch would rebuild and redeploy the app.
     Default watched: everything EXCEPT docs/, tests/, .claude/, .github/, and *.md.
     Because it lives in the repo, this can never drift from the Railway dashboard —
     config-as-code overrides the UI.
     If this app SERVES markdown or files from those paths as runtime content
     (e.g. a docs site that renders docs/**, or tests fixtures served live), remove
     the matching `!` line from railway.json so those changes still deploy, and note
     the exception here. -->

